            <div type="edition" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="grc">
                <ab>
                    <lb n="1"/>ἐσθλὸν ἐν ἀγκοίνησιν ἔχ<supplied reason="lost">ω ξένο</supplied>ν, ὦ παροδίτα
                    <lb n="2"/>φῶτα Ποσείδερμον, Μασσαλ<supplied reason="lost">ίη</supplied>ς ναέτην
                    <lb n="3"/>Πυθαγόρεω φίλον υἷα τὸν ἐνθάδ<supplied reason="lost">ε μ</supplied>οῖρα κραταιὴ
                    <lb n="4"/>πλάγξασα ἐκ πάτρης τῆλε φίλ<supplied reason="lost">ης ὄ</supplied>λεσεν
                </ab>
            </div>
            <div type="apparatus">
                <listApp><app><note>Text of Manni Piraino</note></app></listApp>
            </div>
            <div type="translation" xml:lang="it" resp="ManniPiraino">
                <p>Tengo fra le braccia, o passeggero, un eccellente uomo straniero, Poseidermos, abitante di Marsiglia e figlio caro di Pitagora, che la Moira violenta ha ucciso dopo averlo trascinato lungi dalla cara patria</p>
            </div>
            <div type="commentary">
                <p><!--commented out pending revision-->
                    <!--funerary column, with elegiac distychs (two pairs) engraved on a block across the middle; the whole is stuccoed, the letters were coloured in in a red-brown; Poseidermos, inhabitant of Massalia, son of Pythagoras, whom the fates (moira) killed violently away from home.--></p>
            </div>
